AGI - "The principles of equality and non-discrimination >, enshrined in our Constitution, are an indispensable precondition for the progress of any democratic society and for the full realization of every human person." Thus the President of the Republic, Sergio Mattarella, in a statement issued on the occasion of the International Day against Homophobia, Transphobia and Biphobia.
&nbsp;
"There are more than sixty countries in the world where homosexuality is punished by imprisonment, in some still there is even the death penalty. Intolerance for the different, indifference in the face of compressions of other freedoms, constitute lacerations to democratic coexistence", adds the head of the State.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;"Italy is not immune from episodes of homotransfobia>: discriminated people, crushed by prejudices, who often turn into unacceptable hate speeches, verbally and physically assaulted. It is not possible to accept resigning to brutality" - he continued -&nbsp; "The violence of judgments, > of which many citizens are victims only for their sexual orientation, is an offence for the whole community".
&nbsp;
"The commitment of the institutions must be oriented to provide, above all to the new generations, the tools to understand the diversity of human existences and experiences, for an inclusive and respectful society of identity," Mattarella concludes.

